race.description: Sportsbet Riziz Series Final C,G&E Handicap
race.comment: Good luck, punters. Does it get any harder to find a winner in the last? Each-way odds the field in opening markets with many given a chance here. Perhaps VINTAGE STAR (9) is ready to win after a couple of OK runs this spring. He's a hard horse to catch but he does boast obvious ability and his last start effort over 1050m was full of merit. MURPH (4) is flying, having won consecutive races over 1100m and 1250m. He draws perfectly and will again get the run of the race. He looks a winning threat. OVERSTRIKE (5) is another last-start winner that deserves plenty of thought. Big weight is a worry but he does race best fresh and he's four weeks between runs. You cannot dismiss Victorian raider BIG WATCH (2), who gets Pannell on from a good draw, while THREATENING (17) can go into quaddies at a big price.
